- **Description**: The `onMetadataUpdate()` method handles cluster metadata changes and calls `handleTopicsDeletion()` to clean up offsets for deleted topics. This is complex logic with NO dedicated test coverage. The untested scenarios include: (1) Propagating metadata updates to runtime, (2) Extracting deleted topic IDs from delta, (3) Scheduling write-all operations for multiple deleted topics, (4) Error handling when offset/state cleanup fails, (5) Concurrent metadata updates during offset operations. Topic deletion is a critical operation that must clean up all committed offsets.
